A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Reverend Dr. Augustus T. Curry; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Reverend Dr. Augustus T. Curry has demonstrated his commitment to teaching
3 the Gospel, witnessing Christ through word and deed, and addressing the physical,
4 psychological, intellectual, and spiritual needs of others; and
5 WHEREAS, he currently serves as the founding pastor of Cornerstone Baptist Church PTC,
6 which he established in January 2010 with a mission to strive for excellence in worship,
7 witness, and work; and
8 WHEREAS, under his visionary leadership, Cornerstone Baptist Church PTC grew from
9 holding worship services in leased spaces to securing a permanent worship facility on a
10 21-acre campus in Fayette County, Georgia, within three years of its founding; and
11 WHEREAS, Reverend Curry is a third-generation Baptist preacher who was licensed to
12 preach in 1993 and ordained in 1998 by Emmanuel Baptist Church and the Salem Baptist
13 District Association of Chicago, Illinois, and he has since shared the Gospel of Jesus Christ
14 across the nation; and
