15 WHEREAS, as testament to his exemplary spiritual service, he was honored in March 2014
16 when he was inducted into the distinguished Martin Luther King Jr. Board of Preachers of
17 Morehouse College; and
18 WHEREAS, Reverend Curry further serves as a member of the State Bar of Georgia and has
19 made significant contributions as a noted trial attorney, including his service as legal advisor
20 for the Legal Redress Commission of the Fayette County N.A.A.C.P.; and
21 WHEREAS, it is abundantly fitting and proper to recognize the outstanding accomplishments
22 of the dynamic Christian ministry of this devout and pious man.
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
24 the members of this body recognize and commend Reverend Dr. Augustus T. Curry for his
25 many years of dedicated service on behalf of his fellow citizens as well as extend best wishes
26 for continued success.
27 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
28 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to
29 Reverend Dr. Augustus T. Curry.
